{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Lab 1: Text Embeddings for Marketing\n",
    "**MKTS 420 — Introduction to Deep Learning for Marketing | University of Liverpool**\n",
    "\n",
    "**Core intuition:** Embeddings transform words and sentences into points in high-dimensional space,\n",
    "where *similar meanings are geometrically close*.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Marketing application:** Customer reviews, social posts, and brand descriptions\n",
    "can be embedded and compared — without any hand-crafted rules.\n",
    "\n",
    "**No calculus required.** We focus on: input → representation → output."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Cell 1: Imports and seed\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "from sklearn.decomposition import PCA\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics.pairwise import cosine_similarity\n",
    "\n",
    "np.random.seed(42)\n",
    "sns.set_theme(style='whitegrid', palette='colorblind')\n",
    "plt.rcParams.update({'figure.dpi': 150, 'font.size': 11})\n",
    "print('Ready')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 1: Load a pre-trained sentence embedding model\n",
    "\n",
    "We use `sentence-transformers` — a library that wraps transformer models\n",
    "and returns a single vector per sentence.\n",
    "\n",
    "The model (`all-MiniLM-L6-v2`) was trained on 1 billion sentence pairs.\n",
    "We are *not* training it — we are using it as a feature extractor.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Analogy:** Like using a pre-trained oven (the model) to cook your own ingredients (your text)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from sentence_transformers import SentenceTransformer\n",
    "\n",
    "# This downloads ~90MB on first run, then caches locally\n",
    "model = SentenceTransformer('all-MiniLM-L6-v2')\n",
    "print(f'Model loaded. Embedding dimension: {model.get_sentence_embedding_dimension()}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Marketing review examples — mix of positive, negative, neutral\n",
    "reviews = [\n",
    "    # Positive\n",
    "    'Excellent product, would buy again',\n",
    "    'Fantastic quality, really happy with my purchase',\n",
    "    'Great value for money, fast delivery',\n",
    "    # Negative\n",
    "    'Terrible experience, never coming back',\n",
    "    'Very disappointed, product broke after one week',\n",
    "    'Poor customer service and slow delivery',\n",
    "    # Neutral / mixed\n",
    "    'Product is okay, nothing special',\n",
    "    'Average experience, met expectations',\n",
    "    # Brand-specific\n",
    "    'Love the brand values and sustainability mission',\n",
    "    'The influencer promotion felt authentic and relevant',\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "labels = ['pos', 'pos', 'pos', 'neg', 'neg', 'neg', 'neutral', 'neutral', 'brand', 'influencer']\n",
    "\n",
    "# Embed all reviews — returns a matrix of shape (10, 384)\n",
    "embeddings = model.encode(reviews)\n",
    "print(f'Embedding matrix shape: {embeddings.shape}')\n",
    "print('Each row = one review. Each column = one dimension of meaning.')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 2: Visualise the embedding space\n",
    "\n",
    "384 dimensions is impossible to plot. We use **PCA** to compress to 2D.\n",
    "\n",
    "PCA finds the two directions of maximum variation in the data.\n",
    "Think of it as finding the best angle to view a 3D sculpture from."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "pca = PCA(n_components=2, random_state=42)\n",
    "coords = pca.fit_transform(embeddings)\n",
    "\n",
    "colour_map = {'pos': '#2ecc71', 'neg': '#e74c3c', 'neutral': '#95a5a6',\n",
    "              'brand': '#3498db', 'influencer': '#9b59b6'}\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(9, 6))\n",
    "for i, (review, label) in enumerate(zip(reviews, labels)):\n",
    "    ax.scatter(coords[i, 0], coords[i, 1], color=colour_map[label], s=100, zorder=3)\n",
    "    ax.annotate(\n",
    "        review[:35] + '...' if len(review) > 35 else review,\n",
    "        (coords[i, 0], coords[i, 1]),\n",
    "        fontsize=7.5, xytext=(5, 5), textcoords='offset points'\n",
    "    )\n",
    "\n",
    "# Legend\n",
    "for label, colour in colour_map.items():\n",
    "    ax.scatter([], [], color=colour, label=label.capitalize(), s=80)\n",
    "ax.legend(fontsize=9)\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.set_title('Positive and negative reviews cluster separately in embedding space', fontweight='bold')\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel(f'PC1 ({pca.explained_variance_ratio_[0]*100:.1f}% variance)')\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel(f'PC2 ({pca.explained_variance_ratio_[1]*100:.1f}% variance)')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig('../../../outputs/figures/lab1_embedding_pca.png', dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 3: Cosine similarity — comparing reviews mathematically\n",
    "\n",
    "Cosine similarity measures the angle between two vectors.\n",
    "- Score = 1.0 → identical meaning\n",
    "- Score = 0.0 → unrelated\n",
    "- Score = −1.0 → opposite meaning\n",
    "\n",
    "**Marketing use case:** Find all reviews semantically similar to a brand complaint,\n",
    "without needing to match exact keywords."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Similarity matrix\n",
    "sim_matrix = cosine_similarity(embeddings)\n",
    "\n",
    "short_labels = [r[:25] + '..' if len(r) > 25 else r for r in reviews]\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 8))\n",
    "sns.heatmap(\n",
    "    sim_matrix,\n",
    "    xticklabels=short_labels,\n",
    "    yticklabels=short_labels,\n",
    "    annot=True, fmt='.2f', cmap='RdYlGn',\n",
    "    vmin=0, vmax=1, ax=ax, annot_kws={'size': 7}\n",
    ")\n",
    "ax.set_title('Cosine similarity — positive reviews cluster together (top-left block)', fontweight='bold')\n",
    "plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right', fontsize=7)\n",
    "plt.yticks(fontsize=7)\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig('../../../outputs/figures/lab1_similarity_heatmap.png', dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  }
 ],
